<subSubSection id="C3674785FFA9294A1AC0D80E553AFA28" pageId="3" pageNumber="334" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC2140EFFA9294A1AC0D80E553AFA28" blockId="3.[151,1437,463,1533]" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis id="B909C81CFFA9294A1AC0D80E5776FAD5" bold="true" box="[199,325,1292,1317]" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">Discussion</emphasis>
. The new species belongs to the group of species bearing comb-like ventral clawlets (
<emphasis id="B909C81CFFA9294A1F10D80F53A0FAD4" box="[1303,1427,1293,1316]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">mysorensis</emphasis>
- like species, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC69FFFFA9294A1B56D82D5412FAB8" box="[337,545,1327,1352]" pageId="3" pageNumber="334" refId="ref7327" refString="Goldschmidt, T. (2008) Taxonomical, ecological and zoogeographical studies on anisitsiellid water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia: Anisitsiellidae Koenike, 1910) from Madagascar. Zootaxa, 1954, 1 - 120." type="journal article">Goldschmidt 2008</bibRefCitation>
for discussion). The new species from 
<collectingCountry id="F36A549EFFA9294A19DFD8335206FAB9" box="[984,1077,1329,1353]" name="Mayotte" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">Mayotte</collectingCountry>
differs from all other species of this group by the characteristic ventral projection at P-4. The only species with a similarly shaped P-4, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D6F8DFFA9294A1F80D85757D8FA60" authority="K. Viets, 1914" authorityName="K. Viets" authorityYear="1914" class="Arachnida" family="Anisitsiellidae" genus="Platymamersopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nordenskioeldi">
<emphasis id="B909C81CFFA9294A1F80D857570EFA60" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">P. nordenskioeldi</emphasis>
K. Viets, 1914
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F36A549EFFA9294A1833D87A549AFA60" box="[564,681,1400,1424]" name="Cameroon" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F36A549EFFA9294A18E4D8755507FA60" box="[739,820,1399,1424]" name="Liberia" pageId="3" pageNumber="334">Liberia</collectingCountry>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC69FFFFA9294A1974D87555C6FA60" box="[883,1013,1399,1424]" pageId="3" pageNumber="334" refId="ref7076" refString="Cook, D. R. (1966) The water mites of Liberia. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 6, 1 - 418." type="journal article">Cook 1966</bibRefCitation>
), differs in simple dorsal and ventral clawlets on I–III-L, a large, rounded dorsal shield, a very short coxal field, not protruding over the frontal margin, and a more concave ventral margin of P-2 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEC69FFFFA9294A187CD8BD54CEFA28" box="[635,765,1471,1496]" pageId="3" pageNumber="334" refId="ref7076" refString="Cook, D. R. (1966) The water mites of Liberia. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 6, 1 - 418." type="journal article">Cook 1966</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
